cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the problem of natural language object retrieval, which involves understanding both visual and textual information. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) categories. The paper also proposes a deep reinforcement learning approach, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the paper involves training an agent to move and reshape a bounding box, which is related to Robotics (cs.RO).
